[[File:60 Years of Victory in the Great Patriotic War reverse.jpg|120px|thumb|right|Reverse of the Jubilee Medal "60 Years of Victory in the Great Patriotic War 1941-1945"]]
The '''Jubilee Medal "60 Years of Victory in the Great Patriotic War 1941-1945"''' (Russian: <U+042E><U+0431><U+0438><U+043B><U+0435><U+0439><U+043D><U+0430><U+044F> <U+043C><U+0435><U+0434><U+0430><U+043B><U+044C> <U+00AB>60 <U+043B><U+0435><U+0442> <U+041F><U+043E><U+0431><U+0435><U+0434><U+044B> <U+0432> <U+0412><U+0435><U+043B><U+0438><U+043A><U+043E><U+0439> <U+041E><U+0442><U+0435><U+0447><U+0435><U+0441><U+0442><U+0432><U+0435><U+043D><U+043D><U+043E><U+0439> <U+0432><U+043E><U+0439><U+043D><U+0435> 1941-1945 <U+0433><U+0433>.<U+00BB>) is a state commemorative medal of the [[Russian Federation]]. It was established to denote the 60th anniversary of the 1945 victory over [[Nazi Germany]].

==Medal History ==
The Jubilee Medal "60 Years of Victory in the Great Patriotic War 1941-1945" was established on February 28, 2004 by [[Presidential Decree]] <U+2116> 277<ref name="decree277">{{cite web | authorlink = Russian Government | title = Decree of the President of the Russian Federation of February 28, 2004 No 277  | publisher = Simple Law (Russia) <U+0417><U+0430><U+043A><U+043E><U+043D> <U+041F><U+0440><U+043E><U+0441><U+0442> | date = 2004-02-28 | url = http://zakonprost.ru/content/base/part/369081 | format = HTML | language = Russian | accessdate =2012-02-18}} </ref>.

== Medal Statute ==
The Jubilee Medal "60 Years of Victory in the Great Patriotic War 1941-1945" is awarded to veterans of the Armed Forces of the [[USSR]] who participated in the fighting in the [[Great Patriotic War]], [[guerrillas]], the [[Resistance during World War II|Underground]], those awarded the [[Medal for the Victory Over Germany in the Great Patriotic War 1941<U+2013>1945|Medal for victory over Germany in the Great Patriotic War of 1941-1945]] or [[Medal For the Victory Over Japan|For the Victory over Japan]],  persons awarded for their selfless work the medal [[Valiant Labour in the Great Patriotic War of 1941<U+2013>1945 Medal|"For Valiant Labour in the Great Patriotic War"]] or "Citizen of the siege of Leningrad" or any of the "Defence" medals of the cities or regions of the [[USSR]]; to persons who worked in the period from 22 June 1941 to May 9, 1945 for no less than six months, excluding the period of work in the temporarily [[occupied territories]]; former under-age prisoners of concentration camps, ghettos and other places of detention established by the Nazis and their allies; foreign nationals from outside the [[Commonwealth of Independent States]] who fought in the national military forces in the USSR, as part of guerilla units, underground groups, and other anti-fascist groups who have made significant contribution to victory in the Great Patriotic War and who were awarded state awards of the USSR or Russian Federation<ref name="statute">{{cite web | authorlink = Russian Government | title = Statute of the Jubilee Medal "60 Years of Victory in the Great Patriotic War 1941-1945" | publisher = Commission under the President of the Russian Federation on state awards | date = 2004-02-28 | url = http://award.adm.gov.ru/medal/medal_19.htm | format = HTML | language = Russian | accessdate =2012-02-18}} </ref>.

Presidential Decree 1099 of September 7, 2010<ref name="decree1099">{{cite web  | authorlink = Russian Government | title = Decree of the President of the Russian Federation of September 7, 2010 No 1099 | publisher = Russian Gazette | date = 2010-09-07 | url = http://www.rg.ru/2010/09/15/nagrady-dok.html | format = HTML | language = Russian | accessdate =2012-02-18}}</ref> dictates that although bestowed by the state, that commemorative medals were no longer to be considered "awards" in the distinction/reward sense of the word, but were solely for the purpose of denoting a special event, date or person.

== Medal Description ==
The Jubilee Medal "60 Years of Victory in the Great Patriotic War 1941-1945" is a 32mm in diameter [[tombac]] circular medal.  Its [[obverse]] bears the relief image of the [[Order of Victory]], at the bottom, the relief numbers "1945-2005".  The reverse bears the inscription in seven lines "60 Years of Victory in the Great Patriotic War of 1941-1945" ({{lang-ru|"60 <U+043B><U+0435><U+0442> <U+041F><U+043E><U+0431><U+0435><U+0434><U+044B> <U+0432> <U+0412><U+0435><U+043B><U+0438><U+043A><U+043E><U+0439> <U+041E><U+0442><U+0435><U+0447><U+0435><U+0441><U+0442><U+0432><U+0435><U+043D><U+043D><U+043E><U+0439> <U+0432><U+043E><U+0439><U+043D><U+0435> 1941-1945"}}) within a laurel wreath.<ref name="statute"/>

The medal is suspended by a ring through the award's suspension loop to a standard Russian pentagonal mount covered with an overlapping 24mm wide red silk moir<U+00E9> ribbon with 5mm edge [[Ribbon of Saint George|Ribbons of Saint George]].<ref name="statute"/>

